<div class='m-only'>
<h3 class='mt-0'>SXSW 2017</h3>
</div>
<div class='idea-block idea-voting m-only'>
</div>
<div class='idea-block idea-overview'>
<h2>Cognitive UX</h2>
<p id='idea_description'><p>Imagine a day when user experience is no longer set in stone; rather, it is cognitive, highly personalized to you and dynamically adaptive to your intent, mood, behavior and context. A home screen that knows which apps you're most likely to use right now and reorganize them accordingly. A notification center that knows when to (and not to) disturb you. A productivity app that knows what tool bars are most relevant to your work at hand. That day is coming soon. In this session, we will offer our point of view on Cognitive UX and discuss with the audience its mindset, use cases, design principles and building blocks.</p></p>
</div>
<div class='idea-block idea-share m-only'>
<h4>Share this idea</h4>
